entry.title: Titanic Sub's Deadly Implosion Draws Investigation
entry.content: Officials are undertaking an international investigation into the submersible implosion that killed five adventurers on an expedition to the Titanic.

entry.title: What a Year in Post-Roe America Reveals About Abortion
entry.content: Support for at least some measure of rights, even in red states, has scrambled political dynamics and divided abortion opponents. Kansas “was the first alarm bell that went off, ” said a longtime abortion opponent from Oklahoma.

entry.title: Ukraine Shoots Down Russian Cruise-Missile Barrage
entry.content: Kyiv’s forces also fought off a Russian ground attack in the country’s east amid a slowdown in their effort to recapture occupied parts of the country.
